  <static seed="224" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring515.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{27-3t^{2}}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>3\mathopen{}\left(3+t\right)\mathopen{}\left(3-t\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Notice that <m>3</m> is common to both terms, so let<rsq/>s begin by factoring 
that from both terms; the resulting expression is  the <em>difference of squares</em></p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {27-3t^{2}} \amp  = 3(3^2-{t}^2)\\
                            \amp  = {3\mathopen{}\left(3+t\right)\mathopen{}\left(3-t\right)}
            \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
